Raffles Medical Plans to Open Clinic in Osaka, Nikkei Reports

-- B y   M a s a t s u g u   H o r i e
-- 
2011-06-03T01:51:18Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-03/raffles-medical-plans-to-open-clinic-in-osaka-nikkei-reports.html
Raffles Medical Group Ltd. (RFMD)  plans to
open a medical clinic in Osaka to meet demand from wealthy Asian
travelers and foreign business people, The Nikkei newspaper
reported.  The Singapore-based health care provider is in talks with
Hanshin Electric Railway Co., a local railway operator, and a
real estate developer owned by  Hankyu Hanshin Holdings Inc. (9042)  to
set up the clinic, mostly likely in the Umeda business district,
Nikkei reported, without saying where it got the information.  The Osaka clinic, to be staffed by English-speaking doctors
and nurses, would be the companyâ€™s first in  Japan , the report
said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
